spanishExample: Lo ha probado y lo odia.
englishTranslation: She has tried it and she hates it.

spanishExample: Trabaja duro hora tras hora.
englishTranslation: He works hard hour after hour.

spanishExample: En base a eso, empecé a trabajar con ellos.
englishTranslation: Based on that, I started working with them.

spanishExample: Quiero probarla, sin embargo, la mayoría fue comida.
englishTranslation: I want to try it (f); however, the majority was eaten.

spanishExample: Esa pareja junto a la puerta no quiere tener una conversación conmigo.
englishTranslation: That couple next to the door doesn't want to have a conversation with me.

spanishExample: Al parecer, ese ruido no es de la música sino de la conversación.
englishTranslation: Apparently, that noise isn’t from the music but from the conversation.

spanishExample: Lamento sentarme junto a ti.
englishTranslation: I’m so sorry to sit next to you.

spanishExample: Quiero que empiece a trabajar con esos proyectos, salvo este.
englishTranslation: I want her to start working with those projects, except for this one.

spanishExample: ¡Salve la casa! ¡Tiene una sola habitación!
englishTranslation: (Formal) Save the house! It has just one bedroom!

spanishExample: No salvó a una persona sino a cinco.
englishTranslation: He didn’t save one person but rather five.

spanishExample: Anda tras la política.
englishTranslation: He is going after politics.

spanishExample: Creo que ese sonido está en inglés, pero él no quiere que yo tema.
englishTranslation: I think that sound is in English, but he doesn’t want me to fear.

spanishExample: Estamos empezando a trabajar con el mayor tamaño.
englishTranslation: We’re starting to work with the biggest size.

spanishExample: Si pruebas esta, puedes comerlas todas, salvo esa.
englishTranslation: If you try this one(f), you can eat them all(f), except that one(f).

spanishExample: No quiere que la odie, no en ese estado.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t want me to hate her, not in that state.

spanishExample: La casa frente a la mía tiene una sola habitación.
englishTranslation: The house opposite mine has just one bedroom.

spanishExample: Empezamos a trabajar con la base y la pusimos al lado de ese edificio.
englishTranslation: We started working with the base and we put it beside that building.

spanishExample: Quiero que esté a salvo ante cualquier problema.
englishTranslation: I want him to be safe in the face of any problem.

spanishExample: Esa posición frente a esto no es buena.
englishTranslation: That position opposite this isn’t good.

spanishExample: La vi, salva y tranquila.
englishTranslation: I saw her, safe and calm.

spanishExample: Si lo salvo, puede empezar una nueva vida.
englishTranslation: If I save him, he can start a new life.

spanishExample: ¡Prueba esta comida y luego empieza a trabajar!
englishTranslation: Try this food and then start working!

spanishExample: Empezamos una nueva red de amigos, salvos y felices.
englishTranslation: We’re starting a new network of friends, safe and happy.

spanishExample: Si empieza a trabajar ahora, quizás salve el proyecto.
englishTranslation: If she starts working now, maybe she’ll save the project.

spanishExample: Al parecer, tienes que ser fuerte ante los problemas.
englishTranslation: Apparently, you have to be strong in the face of problems.

spanishExample: Ha salvado a muchas personas del edificio al lado de este.
englishTranslation: She has saved a lot of people from the building beside this one.

spanishExample: No odio nada, salvo la tarea.
englishTranslation: I don’t hate anything, except homework.
